Actor Sam Phillips has died at the age of 72. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Veteran film and stage actor Sam Phillips has died. The 72-year old was a writer, music composer, director and producer. He is best known for his role as Odwa on the eighth season of the SABC-1 drama series Soul City. The veteran recently played the role of Samuel, on Kings Of Joburg on Netflix. Phillips also wrote the lyrics for the film Bopha directed byÂ Morgan Freeman.